==English==

===Etymology===
From the Latin ''[[brumalis]]'', from ''[[bruma]]'' (meaning [[winter]]) which is a contraction of ''[[brevima]]'', (meaning ‘the shortest day’).

===Adjective===
'''brumal'''

# belonging to winter; winterlike
# characteristic or related to winter
# occuring in winter

====Related terms====
*[[brume]]
*[[brumous]]

